bio.experienceSummary:
Hi there! My name is Balasia and I am currently a senior at Rutgers University. I will be receiving my bachelors degree in Social Work, May of 2023, and I am looking for a nanny job to support me along the way!

I am very passionate about working with youth and families! Since the age of 16, I have worked in day care centers and elementary schools. Throughout my professional and academic journey, I have expanded my experience to working with middle school & high school aged children. Outside of my professional experience, I am the youngest of 7 children and I have many nieces and nephews. I am a proud aunt!

I hope that can find some time to connect & get to know more about one another!

description.displayText: Balasia was the best babysitter I've had as of yet. She's always on time and prepared for the day. Not only is she great at her job but she's extremely fun to be around even for my husband and I, very mature and professional. Sadly, we moved so the kids (ages 5-8) miss her so much already.

bio.experienceSummary: I grew up in a big family both immediate and extended. I am the oldest of seven and I have been surrounded by babies/young children my entire life. I also babysit at school. I have been with that family for almost two years now and continue to have a good relationship with them. I am trustworthy, responsible, and reliable.

description.displayText: Kayleigh has been our babysitter for the past 4 years.  My kids love it when she watches them because she is fun, plays games with them and has even taken them out to dinner. We have had such a great experience with Kayleigh. She is reliable and responsible and a great role model. We are lucky to have her and your family would be too.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello, My name is Marlen. I am very interested in the position. I live in Clark, NJ . I have 15+ years in experience caring for children, starting as a babysitter at the age of 15 to now having the experience of a mom. I always try to follow or set a schedule for young children as they thrive well with schedules set. I am currently a mom of a 6-year-old daughter. I would be able to bring your child to activities in the library and have fun time at the parks as well. I thrive in helping young children achieve their milestones even at a young age and celebrate those milestones to help encourage them even more. I am bilingual, speaking english and spanish. I would also encourage your child to grow up bilingual as well.

I love kids and kids love me! I have a lot of experience babysitting and nannying for families with children of all ages. I have had experience working at a daycare center in the preschool and infant rooms. I have also worked as a camp counselor for over 5 years at various performing arts camps and programs, and interned as an English TA at a high school in Vienna, Austria. The children I work with love me because am just as fun and imaginative as they are. Here is a poem one of my 12 yr old Austrian students wrote for me: Singer, Active, Much Fun, Always happy, Natural, Theater, Honest.

I am looking for a part time nanny position with consistent hours that work with my grad school schedule.

Starting in May or June (possibly sooner), I will be available to work full days Wednesday-Friday.

description.originalText: Sam has been caring for our daughter since she was 7 months old (she is now 2!) and has been so wonderful. She is gentle, sweet, caring, and attentive. She drives my daughter weekly to classes and is always careful and cautious. She handles meltdowns and tantrums with calmness and ease, which is especially helpful for the big feelings our 2 year old has. She has been such a help to our family.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! My name is Citlalli A :) I'm a positive and energetic college student. I am currently a teacher assistant at a daycare! I love working with kids. I'm looking for a way to earn a little extra money while doing the thing I love. I'm confident, energetic, and fun. I will be more than happy to meet you and your kiddo soon!

I am an extremely responsible, nurturing and patient person. I enjoy working with kids & being a positive influence. I am a former au pair from South Africa. I am currently pursuing my dream of studying Education in the United States. I am always ready for a challenge and firmly believe in rules as they are there to guide and protect us. I can be assertive, but I can also be playful and fun. I firmly believe in always taking my responsibilities and duties very seriously. The safety and happiness of the children is my highest priority. Staying calm and rational during stressful situations are two of my strengths. I will ensure I give them enough individual attention that they require. I am both mature and dependable.

I'm a friendly and patient childcare provider with 3 years of experience. My passion is supporting families by providing reliable care for their children. I prioritize open communication with parents, offering regular updates throughout the day.

I'm comfortable caring for one child at a time and am happy to help with light housekeeping. I'm also certified in First Aid Training.

With me, your child will have a blast! I love playing outdoor sports and physical games, board games and puzzles, and even technology-based games and apps. I believe that play is essential for a child's development and learning.

I look forward to meeting you and your family!

I am a nurturing and responsible 20-year-old mom with extensive hands-on childcare experience.
Naturally compassionate and highly dependable, I combine personal insight with professional skills to
create a safe, engaging, and enriching environment for children. My patience, creativity, and love for nurturing young minds makes me an excellent choice for a nanny role.

I believe in open communication with parents and will provide regular updates on your child's day, using your preferred method of communication. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules to ensure a safe and structured environment.

From outdoor sports and physical games to board games and puzzles, I enjoy a wide range of activities that promote learning and fun. I'm confident that I can provide your children with a stimulating and enjoyable experience.

I have a car, am comfortable with pets, and am CPR and First Aid certified.

Hi my name is Gia I'm 28 years old, I have a bachelor in communications and a masters in child development. I have worked with children for many years. When getting my bachelor I worked for one family just watching their two children after school. Once summer hit they went to camp, they were also pretty big so they only needed me for the year. For the rest of my bachelor I worked with two boys in Westfield that I loved. After them I started working in day cares with babies and young children which are my favorite. Once Covid hit I choose to go back to school online and become a full time nanny Now I have my own baby. I'm looking for a family that will let me watch their child with my own child. He is 3 months old and super easy going. I have a lot of experience handing many children at once, so I believe I would be able to give mine and your what they need.

Positive, calm, balanced, committed, ambitious, compassionate, reliable, kind and very creative. My 2 daughters are my highest achievement making me proud every single day. In the past I worked as a Art teacher for kids with disabilities at "Special School Sacel" Romania. Between 2000 and 2005 I was part of an amazing French nonprofit organization "L'École de clown" where I was doing art therapy with homeless kids. I am in the process of getting a degree in Art Therapy so I could use my creative skills to help kids and adults to express themselves through art. I am very patient, caring and nurturing person, highly skilled in educational activities to stimulate physical, social and cognitive development of the child. I have also worked for many years as a baby sitter and floating lead teacher in daycare setting. Babysit children between 1 month to 10 years old. Recently I received my certification for CPR, First Aid and AED.

description.displayText:
I am writing to express my recommendation for Camelia M. Cami has worked as a babysitter for my two year old toddler for the last 9 months. She serves as an excellent role model to my young child. My daughter always looked forward to her time with Cami and are always very sad to see her leave. She used to do lot of great art work and read her books and teach her lessons of life. 
She is a very kind and responsible person. She has never given me reason to believe that she could not handle any situation that was put before her. You would be very fortunate to hire her as an employee
